===============
Version 2.17.90
===============

  Code name:

	* "Soup for the troops"

  Features:

	* Sabayon comes back from the dead.  It's dark, mysterious,
          and *pissed off*.

	* Has a chance of working; there were major bugs in how the
          list of configuration changes gets applied.

  Fixes:

	* Many installation and build system fixes, including fixes
          for 64-bit platforms (Alex Larsson, Kjartan Maraas)

	* http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=331615
	  Put the right categories in sabayon.desktop (Wouter Bolsterlee)

	* http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=320589
	  Use better descriptions for changes to the panel
	  (Sayamindu Dasgupta)

	* https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=230018
	  Commit the list of configuration changes in the right order.
	  (Federico Mena-Quintero)

	* http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=395505
	  Notice creation/removal of directories in child session
	  (Hans Petter Jansson)

	* https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=184919
	  Don't use unrobust shell quoting (Hans Petter Jansson)

	* http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=327983
	  Improve "make uninstall" (Joseph Sacco)

	* Fixes for translations (Kjartan Maraas)

  New documentation:

	* API reference: http://sayamindu.randomink.org/sabayon_docs/
	  (Sayamindu Dasgupta)

	* Scripting Sabayon with Python: http://live.gnome.org/PythonSabayon
	  (Sayamindu Dasgupta)

  Translators:

